Task 6: Text and Font

+ Styling Text and Fonts:
      - font-family : Sets the font family.
      - font-size : Sets the font size.
      - font-weight : Sets the font weight (e.g., normal, bold).
      - text-align : Sets the text alignment (e.g., left, center, right).
Example:
HTML
<h1>Heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph with regular text.</p>
<p style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;">This is a bold paragraph.</p>
